Love, it is said, conquers all. But in South Africa, it was not nearly enough to beat the cops at a roadblock enforcing the coronavirus lockdown regulations. So, a Romeo who clearly needed his Juliet to be able to weather the privations of his self-isolation, ended up being arrested for real, when the cops discovered her hiding in the boot of his car, which had been stopped on the N12 highway. He was, it turned, out, trying to smuggle her across the border from Gauteng into Mpumalanga, in defiance of the Disaster Management Act regulations, which prohibit unauthorised travel between...